Sculptor->Slider Manips

This tool allows the user to translate, scale and rotate the selected
object using sliders or typed values. Slider Manips are more precise
than Direct Manips.

It has four components. Click on them to open the interfaces. Click on
the "Style" button to change the style of the interface. Click on the
component bar to close the interface. Each of the components allow
manipulation in one of 3 axes: X, Y and Z. Note that X refers to the
left-right direction, Y is the up-down direction, and Z is the
front-back direction.

"Translations": This allows you to specify the location of the object
with respect to its parent (or the global scene).

"Scales": This allows you to stretch the object along each of the 3
directions (X, Y and Z).

"Rotations": This allows you to rotate the object about any of the 3
axes (X, Y and Z).

"Scale Orientation": This allows you to "shear" (non-uniform
stretching) the object along an axis (X, Y or Z).

"Center": This allows you to specify the center of the object. Any
scaling or rotation is done about this point.
